Norman Ray Harris (October 14, 1947 – March 20, 1987) was an American guitarist, producer, music arranger and songwriter, closely associated with Philly soul.
He was a founding member of MFSB, the Philadelphia studio band, and one of the Baker-Harris-Young record production trio.
In 1980, he released his only solo album, The Harris Machine, on Philadelphia International.
